WEBVTT

00:03.571 --> 00:06.707
[ Soda cans open ]

00:06.740 --> 00:08.842
[ Sighs ]
Oh, no.
Is that what I think it is?

00:08.876 --> 00:11.011
Eddie's making his
"Soda Suicide" again...

00:11.045 --> 00:13.381
* Yeah
...a sugar-coma-inducing blend

00:13.414 --> 00:16.950
of Dr. Pepper, Squirt,
Fanta, Mountain Dew,

00:16.984 --> 00:19.653
and a cherry
Jolly Rancher.

00:19.687 --> 00:22.290
And like always, he's gonna
stumble into the living room

00:22.323 --> 00:24.325
like a drunk uncle
at a wedding...

00:24.358 --> 00:26.160
Plop down on the couch
too hard,

00:26.194 --> 00:27.695
spilling all over
the place.

00:27.728 --> 00:29.497
Not this time.

00:29.530 --> 00:32.133
**

00:32.166 --> 00:34.102
You...

00:34.135 --> 00:36.137
didn't...
spill on the couch?

00:36.170 --> 00:39.840
Nope. As I was about to sit,
I was like...

00:39.873 --> 00:42.143
"What if I put my cup down
on the table first?"

00:42.176 --> 00:45.113
Seems so obvious,
but, hey, live and learn.

00:45.146 --> 00:47.148
He's even using
a coaster.

00:47.181 --> 00:48.349
[ Slurps ]

00:48.382 --> 00:50.118
Ahh. Still got the skills.

00:50.151 --> 00:51.385
I haven't made one of these

00:51.419 --> 00:53.321
since Alison and I
started dating.

00:53.354 --> 00:56.657
[ Scoffs ]
She hated them.

00:56.690 --> 00:58.859
Are you telling me you think
you can make a soda taste better

00:58.892 --> 01:00.027
than the professionals?

01:00.060 --> 01:01.762
Than the flavor engineers
at Mountain Dew?

01:01.795 --> 01:03.231
Than Dr. Melvin Pepper?

01:03.264 --> 01:04.932
He's a damn doctor!

01:04.965 --> 01:06.500
Now that she broke up with me,

01:06.534 --> 01:08.602
I'm focused on
forgetting about her

01:08.636 --> 01:10.504
and just being
the best me I can.

01:10.538 --> 01:13.241
Very mature, son.
I'm proud of you.

01:13.274 --> 01:14.842
Hey, hey, hey.

01:14.875 --> 01:17.077
I'm proud of us.

01:17.111 --> 01:19.613
Do you see
what's happening here?

01:19.647 --> 01:22.183
The last of our three children
has grown up.

01:22.216 --> 01:24.485
We're finally out
of "kid jail."

01:28.656 --> 01:30.291
We can have
nice things again.

01:30.324 --> 01:32.360
[ Chuckles ]
Look at her, Louis.

01:32.393 --> 01:36.063
As beautiful as the day we first
put her in storage in 1982.

01:36.096 --> 01:37.631
I'll never forget
that day.

01:37.665 --> 01:40.067
Your water broke, and I said,
"Let's go to the hospital,"

01:40.100 --> 01:42.336
and you said,
"After we make one stop."

01:42.370 --> 01:44.104
My labor pains
were so intense.

01:44.138 --> 01:46.240
But after three hours
of pushing,

01:46.274 --> 01:47.541
we finally
figured out a way

01:47.575 --> 01:49.443
to wedge this couch
into the storage unit.

01:49.477 --> 01:50.878
**

01:50.911 --> 01:54.047
Welcome home,
sweetheart.

01:54.081 --> 01:56.550
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:56.584 --> 01:57.751
* Fresh off the boat

01:57.785 --> 01:59.620
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

01:59.653 --> 02:01.755
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

02:01.789 --> 02:03.157
* Fresh off the boat

02:03.191 --> 02:05.359
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

02:05.393 --> 02:06.927
* But I know where I'm goin'

02:06.960 --> 02:09.663
* I'm fresh off the boat

02:09.697 --> 02:11.699
No way.
Yes way.

02:11.732 --> 02:12.633
The last time we drank

02:12.666 --> 02:13.501
during the day

02:13.534 --> 02:14.202
was 15 years ago

02:14.235 --> 02:14.935
at the racetrack.

02:14.968 --> 02:16.304
You called the cashier a racist

02:16.337 --> 02:17.438
because a horse was named

02:17.471 --> 02:18.472
"Chinese Chicken Salad."

02:18.506 --> 02:20.040
I remember that now!

02:20.073 --> 02:22.176
Wow. We had fun, Louis.

02:22.210 --> 02:24.578
Don't ever let anyone
tell you otherwise.

02:24.612 --> 02:25.813
Well, with Eddie maturing,

02:25.846 --> 02:26.980
we can go back to having fun.

02:27.014 --> 02:28.649
Orlando is the 37th best city

02:28.682 --> 02:29.750
in America for a reason.

02:29.783 --> 02:31.118
Let's start enjoying it.

02:31.151 --> 02:32.586
Okay. What should we do first?

02:32.620 --> 02:34.322
Why don't we see

02:34.355 --> 02:35.889
what Honey and Marvin
are up to tonight?

02:35.923 --> 02:38.158
Let's dial up those fools
and see what's up.

02:38.192 --> 02:40.628
Hey, nice use of slang.

02:40.661 --> 02:41.929
Did it sound dumb?

02:41.962 --> 02:44.265
I've only had half a beer,
but the voice in my head

02:44.298 --> 02:46.434
that criticizes me constantly
has gone quiet.

02:46.467 --> 02:47.901
And you realize
we don't need

02:47.935 --> 02:49.470
to have quick dinners
anymore, right?

02:49.503 --> 02:52.206
We don't need to be afraid
of leaving Eddie unsupervised.

02:52.240 --> 02:54.107
We can finally do more
than just dinner.

02:54.141 --> 02:55.743
We can do "dinner and...".

02:55.776 --> 02:57.010
Dinner and dancing,

02:57.044 --> 02:58.479
dinner and a movie...

02:58.512 --> 03:00.681
dinner and drinks
at a jazz club!

03:00.714 --> 03:01.982
Better idea --

03:02.015 --> 03:04.184
we can invite Honey and Marvin
to dinner and...

03:06.153 --> 03:07.154
...karaoke.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.856
Get them on the phone
immediately.

03:08.889 --> 03:10.791
Ahh! I can't wait to sing
some Mariah.

03:10.824 --> 03:11.825
She's the only woman

03:11.859 --> 03:12.793
who can match my range.

03:12.826 --> 03:14.628
Hmm.

03:14.662 --> 03:18.899
**

03:18.932 --> 03:19.800
How did that

03:19.833 --> 03:20.768
out-of-control sprinkler

03:20.801 --> 03:22.002
only hit me and not you?

03:22.035 --> 03:22.970
I don't know, bro,

03:23.003 --> 03:24.204
but it's your bad luck year,

03:24.238 --> 03:26.540
so keep your nasty juju
away from me.

03:26.574 --> 03:28.476
I'm gonna go throw my clothes
in the dryer.

03:31.579 --> 03:33.347
Oh, come on!

03:36.183 --> 03:37.718
**

03:37.751 --> 03:39.587
What the hell?

03:39.620 --> 03:41.322
Alison,
what are you doing here?

03:41.355 --> 03:43.223
Why wouldn't she be here?
We're friends.

03:43.257 --> 03:44.825
Since when are you friends?

03:44.858 --> 03:45.893
Eddie, you know

03:45.926 --> 03:46.994
how you're always
late for everything?

03:47.027 --> 03:48.262
No.

03:48.296 --> 03:50.864
[ Sighs ]

03:50.898 --> 03:53.534
Well, over the years,
when Alison came by our house

03:53.567 --> 03:55.336
and had to wait for you
to arrive,

03:55.369 --> 03:57.505
she and I struck up
a great friendship.

03:57.538 --> 03:58.406
A great friendship?

03:58.439 --> 03:59.206
What do you guys

03:59.239 --> 04:00.007
even talk about?

04:00.040 --> 04:01.241
We talk about Pogs,

04:01.275 --> 04:02.209
Tamagotchis...

04:02.242 --> 04:02.876
Volleyball,

04:02.910 --> 04:04.144
Leno vs. Letterman.

04:04.177 --> 04:06.514
And, you know,
life in general.

04:06.547 --> 04:08.181
What does anyone talk about
with their friends?

04:08.215 --> 04:10.651
Sorry, Eddie, but Evan and I
agreed a long time ago

04:10.684 --> 04:12.185
that if our relationship
ever ended,

04:12.219 --> 04:13.754
me and him would stay friends.

04:13.787 --> 04:15.255
Two crossed arrows

04:15.289 --> 04:16.890
is the universal symbol
for friendship.

04:16.924 --> 04:18.058
Friends forever.

04:18.091 --> 04:20.361
Friends forever.

04:20.394 --> 04:21.495
Your necklaces look cheap.

04:21.529 --> 04:23.263
**

04:23.297 --> 04:25.999
He's not worth it.
You're right.

04:26.033 --> 04:27.735
I'm gonna go see if our
dino nuggets are ready.

04:27.768 --> 04:31.104
When I return,
I hope you're not here.

04:34.375 --> 04:35.343
Why you doing me like this,
girl?

04:35.376 --> 04:35.909
I'm sorry.

04:35.943 --> 04:37.044
I was laying it on thick

04:37.077 --> 04:37.845
for Evan's sake.

04:37.878 --> 04:38.712
He's sensitive --

04:38.746 --> 04:40.348
classic Leno fan --

04:40.381 --> 04:42.383
but, really,
I-I'm uncomfortable being here.

04:42.416 --> 04:44.084
I don't want to make things
harder between us

04:44.117 --> 04:45.886
than they already are.
Then why are you?

04:45.919 --> 04:48.055
Because I can't just abandon
my friendship with Evan.

04:48.088 --> 04:49.289
You and I splitting up --

04:49.323 --> 04:51.191
it's like he's a child
of divorce.

04:51.224 --> 04:52.259
What do you know
about divorce?

04:52.292 --> 04:54.428
My parents are divorced.
They are?

04:54.462 --> 04:56.063
I talked to you about it
all the time!

04:56.096 --> 04:57.297
Well, you say
a lot of things!

04:57.331 --> 04:58.732
Let's just drop it.

04:58.766 --> 05:00.368
Obviously, we need some space
from each other.

05:00.401 --> 05:02.536
Well, that means you and Evan
can't be friends.

05:02.570 --> 05:04.438
Yeah, I-I know.

05:04.472 --> 05:06.239
Let's have a talk with him
tomorrow.

05:06.273 --> 05:08.275
So, if your parents
are divorced...

05:08.308 --> 05:10.310
do you get, like, twice as many
presents at Christmas?

05:11.779 --> 05:14.314
[ Smacks lips ]
We're Jewish.

05:14.348 --> 05:16.584
Huh.

05:16.617 --> 05:19.086
**

05:19.119 --> 05:21.422
I'm so happy
Honey and Marvin

05:21.455 --> 05:22.990
could come
to dinner tonight.

05:23.023 --> 05:25.826
I already pre-paid
for our private karaoke room,

05:25.859 --> 05:27.628
so we are all set.
Thank you for splurging

05:27.661 --> 05:29.262
on the
four-microphone package.

05:29.296 --> 05:31.264
It's important we do
"Lady Marmalade" properly.

05:31.298 --> 05:32.466
[ Laughs ]
I can't wait!

05:32.500 --> 05:34.868
-Hey!
-Oh, hi!

05:34.902 --> 05:37.805
Oh, it's so good to see you.
-Hello, hello.

05:37.838 --> 05:39.172
Oh,
I'm sorry we're late.

05:39.206 --> 05:41.008
Marvin was stuck at work
finishing a dental cleaning...

05:41.041 --> 05:43.811
Uh-huh.
...for a celebrity.

05:43.844 --> 05:45.312
[ Gasps ]
Was it Denzel?

05:45.345 --> 05:48.148
[ Chuckles ] No.
But I will tell you...

05:48.181 --> 05:50.618
she was a joy
to work with.

05:52.352 --> 05:54.622
It was Joy Behar!

05:54.655 --> 05:56.557
Whoa!
Oh, amazing!

05:56.590 --> 05:57.991
Who is that?
[ Mutters ]

05:58.025 --> 05:59.159
Server: Hi.
Welcome to Chez Dennis.

05:59.192 --> 06:00.928
Can I get you all a drink
to start?

06:00.961 --> 06:02.295
I'll have a glass
of red wine.

06:02.329 --> 06:03.464
Pinot gris, please.

06:03.497 --> 06:04.832
[ Chuckles ]
What do you say, Marv,

06:04.865 --> 06:06.734
a couple Negronis
to warm up our engines?

06:06.767 --> 06:07.968
[ Both laugh ]

06:08.001 --> 06:09.302
I-I'll just have
some water.

06:09.336 --> 06:11.905
[ Laughs ]
Hilarious joke, Marvin.

06:11.939 --> 06:14.374
Come on. I've already taken
a dangerous amount of Pepcid AC

06:14.408 --> 06:15.776
to combat
the Asian Flush.

06:15.809 --> 06:17.144
Let's go big tonight!

06:17.177 --> 06:19.513
Uh...actually,
I can't drink because

06:19.547 --> 06:20.814
[Inhales deeply] well...

06:20.848 --> 06:23.383
I'm having
some surgery tomorrow.

06:23.417 --> 06:26.086
Oh, my God.
What for?

06:27.154 --> 06:29.156
I'm having my vasectomy
reversed!

06:29.189 --> 06:30.724
We want to have kids!

06:30.758 --> 06:32.092
[ Both laugh ]

06:37.397 --> 06:38.231
Okay, one last time,
I promise.

06:38.265 --> 06:40.701
Are you sure you want
to have kids?

06:40.734 --> 06:42.736
Because nobody wants
to have kids.

06:42.770 --> 06:44.572
They're just a thing
that happens to you

06:44.605 --> 06:47.140
and then you carry that burden
with you until you die.

06:47.174 --> 06:48.976
My only burden will be keeping
my fingers

06:49.009 --> 06:50.711
from pinching baby legs.

06:50.744 --> 06:53.046
Where's your leg?
Give me your leg.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.515
You nervous about
the surgery?

06:54.548 --> 06:56.249
A reverse vasectomy
sounds intense.

06:56.283 --> 06:57.585
No, no, no.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.419
Uh, it's a simple
outpatient procedure.

06:59.453 --> 07:01.489
They --
They just go down south,

07:01.522 --> 07:04.525
do a little snip-snip,
loosen up my tubes,

07:04.558 --> 07:06.694
and then they take a capillary
out of my neck,

07:06.727 --> 07:09.196
they take that capillary,
fuse it to my tubes,

07:09.229 --> 07:10.998
probably with some kind
of a heat gun,

07:11.031 --> 07:12.265
throw some stitches on it,

07:12.299 --> 07:14.535
and -- boom --
Marvin's shooting bullets.

07:14.568 --> 07:17.404
[ Chuckles ]
Uh-huh. [ Voice cracks ]
Sounds simple.

07:17.437 --> 07:19.573
Louis and I just got sprung
from kid jail,

07:19.607 --> 07:21.041
because Eddie
finally matured,

07:21.074 --> 07:24.277
and it is the best thing
that has ever happened to us.

07:24.311 --> 07:27.180
Why make your life harder...
with a baby?

07:27.214 --> 07:28.916
I don't know.
I think it'll be fun.

07:28.949 --> 07:30.718
I can get it a hat.

07:30.751 --> 07:32.586
Oh, my God.
And the jeans.

07:32.620 --> 07:33.754
For its fat legs.

07:33.787 --> 07:34.955
-Uh, Honey?
-Hmm?

07:34.988 --> 07:36.724
I think it's time for us
to hit the ol' road.

07:36.757 --> 07:39.459
Already? But we were gonna do
dinner and karaoke.

07:39.493 --> 07:42.462
I know, but Marvin needs
to rest up for his procedure,

07:42.496 --> 07:45.833
and I have a gynecologist
appointment tomorrow,

07:45.866 --> 07:48.068
just to make sure things
are good on my end.
[ Laughs ]

07:48.101 --> 07:50.270
I mean, they are,
for sure.

07:50.303 --> 07:51.905
I don't want to get
into details,

07:51.939 --> 07:54.074
but just know that I've never
had a problem getting pregnant.

07:54.107 --> 07:55.609
-All right.
-Bye-bye.

07:55.643 --> 07:56.610
Bye, guys.

07:56.644 --> 07:58.111
**

07:58.145 --> 08:00.280
You know what?
We don't need them.

08:00.313 --> 08:01.481
We can still go out
and have fun.

08:01.515 --> 08:03.416
I did pre-pay.

08:03.450 --> 08:05.686
[ "Opposites Attract" plays ]

08:05.719 --> 08:07.821
* I take
two steps forward *

08:07.855 --> 08:10.190
* I take
two steps back *

08:10.223 --> 08:14.795
* We come together,
'cause opposites attract *

08:14.828 --> 08:16.597
[ Both sigh ]

08:16.630 --> 08:17.965
That was a disgrace
to Paula Abdul

08:17.998 --> 08:19.466
and all that
she stands for.

08:19.499 --> 08:22.169
[ Sighs ]

08:22.202 --> 08:24.371
This just isn't as fun
without Honey and Marvin.

08:24.404 --> 08:26.439
I can't believe the moment
we get out of kid jail,

08:26.473 --> 08:28.241
our best friends decide
to go in.

08:28.275 --> 08:30.077
I was honest with Honey
about how hard it is,

08:30.110 --> 08:31.879
but she wouldn't
even hear it.

08:31.912 --> 08:34.014
She's lost in
baby fever.

08:34.047 --> 08:36.149
She is always quick to dive
into whatever's new.

08:36.183 --> 08:38.786
Remember when she made Marvin
grow sideburns like Luke Perry?

08:38.819 --> 08:40.420
Besides, at Marvin's age,

08:40.453 --> 08:42.656
their baby's gonna come out
4 years old.

08:42.690 --> 08:44.758
Meanwhile, I'm not even
sure he's into the idea
of having a baby.

08:44.792 --> 08:46.827
Is there baby corn
in this salad?

08:46.860 --> 08:47.995
Because if there is,
I don't want it.

08:49.162 --> 08:51.565
He asked
for no baby corn.

08:51.599 --> 08:54.501
Oh, he's definitely not
ready for this!

08:54.534 --> 08:57.337
You can send back baby corn.
You can't send back baby.

08:57.370 --> 08:58.972
I understand Honey
wanting to rush in,

08:59.006 --> 09:00.173
but Marvin's done it before.

09:00.207 --> 09:01.308
He should know better.

09:01.341 --> 09:03.443
You know, if he's even
a little bit unsure,

09:03.476 --> 09:04.712
we should talk to him.

09:04.745 --> 09:06.546
Absolutely.

09:06.580 --> 09:07.848
But first,
let's sing some Michael?

09:07.881 --> 09:09.482
Jackson?
McDonald.

09:09.516 --> 09:10.450
Stipe?

09:10.483 --> 09:11.484
Ooh.

09:11.518 --> 09:14.521
**

09:14.554 --> 09:17.390
We sit before the truest test
of the puzzle master --

09:17.424 --> 09:20.327
the 1,000-piece puzzle
of a bowl of plums.

09:20.360 --> 09:22.896
Every piece is
just purple.

09:22.930 --> 09:24.798
Yes.

09:24.832 --> 09:26.166
Where's Eddie?

09:26.199 --> 09:27.801
He should've been here
45 minutes ago.

09:27.835 --> 09:29.837
Eddie's late?!
I'm stunned!

09:29.870 --> 09:31.538
I know, right?

09:31.571 --> 09:34.808
But we actually have something
serious to talk to you about,

09:34.842 --> 09:37.310
but I guess since he's late,
I'll just tell you.

09:37.344 --> 09:38.545
What is it?

09:38.578 --> 09:39.980
Your brother and I...

09:40.013 --> 09:44.652
well, we both care about you
very much, and...

09:44.685 --> 09:49.422
**

09:49.456 --> 09:50.924
...we're getting back
together!

09:50.958 --> 09:53.026
[ Door opens ]
Shut the front door
and give me a hug!

09:53.060 --> 09:54.561
[ Door closes ]

09:54.594 --> 09:55.696
Sorry I'm late.

09:55.729 --> 09:56.664
I saw a red-tailed fox
on the way home,

09:56.697 --> 09:57.898
so I chased it.

09:57.931 --> 09:59.733
I heard the great news!

09:59.767 --> 10:02.836
I've been hiding some
Nilla Wafers for when
I finish the puzzle,

10:02.870 --> 10:04.705
but what the hay,
let's celebrate!

10:04.738 --> 10:06.073
**

10:06.106 --> 10:07.540
What great news?

10:07.574 --> 10:09.276
I kinda sorta told him
we're getting back together.

10:09.309 --> 10:11.712
What?
You were late,
and I panicked!

10:11.745 --> 10:13.413
[ Sighs ]
Can you tell him
we can't be friends?

10:13.446 --> 10:14.547
No way, ex-boo.

10:14.581 --> 10:16.383
You're the one
who broke up with me.

10:16.416 --> 10:18.686
This was your choice.
You've got to be the bad guy.

10:18.719 --> 10:20.453
[ Sighs ] Fine.

10:20.487 --> 10:21.689
I brought the whole box

10:21.722 --> 10:23.456
in case we want to turn this
into a party.

10:25.292 --> 10:27.728
Evan, there's something else
I have to tell you.

10:27.761 --> 10:30.563
Eddie and I were talking,
and we think it's best if...

10:30.597 --> 10:33.100
**

10:33.133 --> 10:36.103
...we take you
on a pony ride!

10:36.136 --> 10:38.005
[ High-pitched scream ]

10:40.674 --> 10:41.875
[ Screaming continues ]

10:41.909 --> 10:43.443
Grandma!
Emery!

10:43.476 --> 10:44.745
Aah!

10:44.778 --> 10:46.814
My bad luck strikes again.

10:46.847 --> 10:48.281
I can't be around
anyone pouring liquids.

10:57.524 --> 10:58.391
Really?

11:03.897 --> 11:05.432
I thought that was Jesus.

11:12.072 --> 11:14.908
Whoa-ho-ho!
What brings you two over?

11:14.942 --> 11:16.309
I was just on my way
to the hospital.

11:16.343 --> 11:17.377
In a full suit?

11:17.410 --> 11:18.846
Well, I got to show
those docs

11:18.879 --> 11:20.814
that they're operating
on classy merchandise.

11:20.848 --> 11:22.315
Well, we just came by

11:22.349 --> 11:24.317
to see if you needed a ride
to the procedure.

11:24.351 --> 11:25.685
Since Honey has
her appointment,

11:25.719 --> 11:27.054
we figured we could
lend a hand.

11:27.087 --> 11:29.489
There's no need.
I'm gonna drive myself.

11:29.522 --> 11:30.690
We could stop for ice cream
on the way.

11:30.724 --> 11:31.624
Shotgun!

11:31.658 --> 11:35.996
**

11:36.029 --> 11:38.331
The pony's name is Charlie!

11:38.365 --> 11:39.466
Very good!

11:40.667 --> 11:42.002
Sorry I'm late.

11:42.035 --> 11:43.670
How are you late?
We came here together.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.138
I saw some baby ducks

11:45.172 --> 11:46.673
and had to scope out
if there was a pond here.

11:46.706 --> 11:48.008
There wasn't.

11:48.041 --> 11:49.176
I think those ducks
are in trouble.

11:50.377 --> 11:52.145
Isn't his mane beautiful?

11:52.179 --> 11:54.047
Hey, buddy!
Sure is!

11:54.081 --> 11:55.749
By the way,
how'd you find this place?

11:55.783 --> 11:58.485
Um...I know about it because
we came here on our second date.

11:58.518 --> 11:59.686
Whaaat?

12:02.422 --> 12:03.690
Wait.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.725
You keep a picture of us
in your purse?

12:05.759 --> 12:07.394
I thought
you stopped liking me.

12:07.427 --> 12:08.528
We're broken up,

12:08.561 --> 12:10.197
but I'm not trying
to forget you.

12:10.230 --> 12:12.165
It's not like our time together
meant nothing to me.

12:12.199 --> 12:14.067
I know it's my fault
we're here.

12:14.101 --> 12:16.103
I'll tell Evan the truth
as soon as we get back home.

12:16.136 --> 12:18.171
His diet is
mostly carrots!

12:18.205 --> 12:20.808
You don't say!
Great job!

12:22.442 --> 12:24.344
**

12:24.377 --> 12:26.246
So, this is how you want
to spend our time together?

12:26.279 --> 12:28.048
Rearranging shelves?

12:33.053 --> 12:34.054
[ Shatters ]
[ Gasps ]

12:36.423 --> 12:37.825
[ Sighs ]
I'm so sorry.

12:37.858 --> 12:39.226
My stupid bad luck.

12:49.436 --> 12:50.237
[ Mug shatters ]

12:53.606 --> 12:56.709
What, the ice cream place
is in the park?

12:56.743 --> 12:59.412
Yes. It's a truck.
It's very trendy.

12:59.446 --> 13:00.447
[ Chuckling ] Oh.

13:00.480 --> 13:03.650
**

13:03.683 --> 13:05.185
[ Snoring ]

13:05.218 --> 13:09.122
Wow. There are a lot
of homeless people around here.

13:09.156 --> 13:11.892
Oh, those aren't
homeless people.

13:11.925 --> 13:13.927
They're new parents.

13:13.961 --> 13:15.963
Is it time to pump again?

13:15.996 --> 13:17.464
Girl: Mommy!

13:17.497 --> 13:19.099
Mommy!!
[ Gasps ]

13:20.333 --> 13:23.303
[ Cries ]

13:23.336 --> 13:25.138
[ Laughs ]
Why?

13:26.406 --> 13:28.575
Well, what happened
to all of them?

13:28.608 --> 13:31.111
Well, they're exhausted
from taking care of kids.

13:31.144 --> 13:33.013
Feeding them,
changing their diapers.

13:33.046 --> 13:34.647
You remember what
that's like, right?

13:34.681 --> 13:36.216
Right. Right.

13:36.249 --> 13:37.117
You don't know
what I'm talking about,

13:37.150 --> 13:38.418
do you?
I don't!

13:38.451 --> 13:40.153
No, I never experienced
any of this with Nicole.

13:40.187 --> 13:41.321
Her mother did
all the heavy lifting.

13:41.354 --> 13:42.655
I just went to work,
I came home,

13:42.689 --> 13:44.624
watched Carson's monologue,
then went to sleep.

13:44.657 --> 13:47.027
Well, that's not
gonna fly with Honey.

13:47.060 --> 13:48.896
Oh, that's true.
Yeah.

13:48.929 --> 13:51.331
Honey's part of that new,
uh, Generation X

13:51.364 --> 13:52.799
I read about in Newsweek.

13:52.832 --> 13:54.134
They're progressive.

13:54.167 --> 13:57.270
Well, taking care of a baby
today is hard work.

13:57.304 --> 13:59.139
We just want you to be aware
of what you're getting into.

13:59.172 --> 14:00.807
[ Weakly ] Yeah.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.475
[ Quietly ] Baby corn.

14:02.509 --> 14:06.880
**

14:06.914 --> 14:08.415
Jessica:
Well, here we are.

14:08.448 --> 14:10.450
Mm-hmm.
You sure
you're up for this?

14:10.483 --> 14:11.518
Yep.

14:11.551 --> 14:13.620
Already shaved my neck.
[ Chuckles ]

14:13.653 --> 14:16.023
[ Van door opens ]

14:19.026 --> 14:20.560
[ Sighs ]

14:20.593 --> 14:22.795
Well, I guess we were wrong.
He really does want this.

14:22.829 --> 14:23.997
I guess he does.

14:26.066 --> 14:29.769
**

14:29.802 --> 14:30.637
[ Gasps ]

14:30.670 --> 14:34.908
**

14:34.942 --> 14:37.177
I thought he was going
in the hospital, and
then he just turned!

14:37.210 --> 14:38.711
I did not
see that coming!

14:42.649 --> 14:43.650
Thank you. Bye.

14:43.683 --> 14:45.018
Amazing news!

14:45.052 --> 14:47.020
Not only did I book us
the karaoke room

14:47.054 --> 14:48.188
that has
the best acoustics,

14:48.221 --> 14:50.223
I also got us
the four-mic package.

14:50.257 --> 14:51.191
They didn't think
it was available,

14:51.224 --> 14:52.492
but then they checked,
and it was.

14:52.525 --> 14:54.161
I feel really good
about this.

14:54.194 --> 14:55.762
If Marvin wasn't sure
about having kids,

14:55.795 --> 14:57.164
why rush into it?

14:57.197 --> 14:59.399
There's plenty of time.
He's barely 70.

14:59.432 --> 15:01.068
They're lucky to have us
looking out for them.

15:01.101 --> 15:03.536
[ Knock on door ]

15:03.570 --> 15:05.838
So I get home from
my gyno checkup,

15:05.872 --> 15:07.674
which was a huge success.

15:07.707 --> 15:10.443
She compared my uterus to the
fertile shores of Oahu, and...

15:12.779 --> 15:14.881
I'm keeping it.

15:14.914 --> 15:18.518
I'm keeping my vasectomy.

15:18.551 --> 15:20.887
He said he changed his mind,
and he doesn't want a baby.

15:20.920 --> 15:22.022
Right now he doesn't,

15:22.055 --> 15:23.423
but maybe in the future,
he will.

15:23.456 --> 15:25.025
In the meantime,

15:25.058 --> 15:26.859
let's all just
have fun.

15:26.893 --> 15:29.296
Fun sounds fun.
[ Chuckles ]

15:29.329 --> 15:31.598
**

15:31.631 --> 15:33.566
I'll have to cross-reference
my diary,

15:33.600 --> 15:35.635
but I think this is
the best day of my life.

15:37.737 --> 15:38.905
[ Both sigh ]

15:40.540 --> 15:42.809
So, I know we've been having
a lot of fun today,

15:42.842 --> 15:44.978
but we need to talk
about something serious.

15:45.012 --> 15:47.447
Look, your brother
and I --

15:47.480 --> 15:49.649
What I'm trying
to say is...

15:49.682 --> 15:50.850
Gosh, this is so hard.

15:50.883 --> 15:52.752
Alison and I
aren't back together, Evan.

15:52.785 --> 15:54.421
We're still broken up.
[ Gasps ]

15:54.454 --> 15:55.922
I know she lied
and said we're back together,

15:55.955 --> 15:57.224
but it's not her fault.

15:57.257 --> 15:58.491
It's mine.

15:58.525 --> 15:59.692
This all happened because

15:59.726 --> 16:01.761
I didn't want you two
to be friends.

16:01.794 --> 16:04.331
I was trying to forget about her
after our breakup

16:04.364 --> 16:06.799
and when I saw her in the house,
I freaked.

16:06.833 --> 16:08.468
But I realized that...

16:08.501 --> 16:09.802
I don't want to forget
about her.

16:09.836 --> 16:11.371
We had some great times.

16:11.404 --> 16:13.406
So, I want you and her
to be friends.

16:13.440 --> 16:15.708
And hopefully,
she and I can be friends, too.

16:15.742 --> 16:17.144
Yeah.

16:17.177 --> 16:18.945
I think we're gonna be friends,
for sure.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.348
That's sweet.

16:21.381 --> 16:22.649
Here's what I think
of your lies.

16:26.686 --> 16:28.821
Look what you did.

16:28.855 --> 16:30.423
When was the last time
he blinked?

16:32.359 --> 16:34.394
* Don't go breaking
my heart *

16:34.427 --> 16:36.263
* Don't go breaking my

16:36.296 --> 16:38.998
* I won't go breaking
your heart *

16:39.032 --> 16:41.768
[ Chuckles ]

16:41.801 --> 16:45.405
This next song is dedicated
to my uterus.

16:45.438 --> 16:48.641
* All that she wants
is one baby *

16:48.675 --> 16:50.177
* She's gone tomorrow, boy

16:50.210 --> 16:52.612
* All that she wants is

16:52.645 --> 16:55.348
* One baby-a-yay-yay
My body, my choice!

16:55.382 --> 16:58.818
* All that she wants
is one baby *

16:58.851 --> 17:00.620
* She's gone tomor--
Wh-- Sh--

17:00.653 --> 17:03.690
* What you want

17:03.723 --> 17:05.458
* Baby, I got it

17:05.492 --> 17:07.660
* What you need

17:07.694 --> 17:09.462
* You know I got it

17:09.496 --> 17:12.632
What the hell
is happening to you?
* All that I am askin' for

17:12.665 --> 17:14.301
* Is just a little respect
when you get home *

17:14.334 --> 17:16.336
Are they
karaoke fighting?

17:16.369 --> 17:17.970
I don't know,
but I wish you would sing

17:18.004 --> 17:19.706
with this much passion.
* Just a little bit

17:19.739 --> 17:21.374
* Just a -- *
[ Music stops ]

17:21.408 --> 17:23.143
You don't get respect
by changing your mind

17:23.176 --> 17:24.677
last minute about
having a baby!

17:24.711 --> 17:26.646
It's 1997.

17:26.679 --> 17:28.615
You can't tell a man
what to do with his body!

17:28.648 --> 17:29.682
I had doubts.

17:29.716 --> 17:31.118
And -- A-And
Louis and Jessica

17:31.151 --> 17:33.353
helped me confirm my doubts.
They what?

17:33.386 --> 17:34.987
Oh, we just wanted
to remind Marvin

17:35.021 --> 17:36.623
what having a baby
was really like.

17:36.656 --> 17:39.126
It's a big decision --
one that all four of us

17:39.159 --> 17:40.993
need to be 100%
on board for.

17:41.027 --> 17:43.196
I can't believe this.

17:46.032 --> 17:47.500
[ Sighs ]
[ "Funkytown" plays ]

17:47.534 --> 17:48.701
Oh, sorry.

17:48.735 --> 17:50.637
I had this queued up
like 10 minutes ago.

17:52.305 --> 17:56.709
* Gotta make a move to a town
that's right for me *

17:56.743 --> 17:59.412
**

18:01.448 --> 18:04.851
Mahjong!
This is gonna be so much fun.

18:04.884 --> 18:06.786
Throw the tiles around...

18:06.819 --> 18:09.456
[ Gasps, laughs ]

18:20.767 --> 18:24.671
I am plotzing.
These tiles are caliente!

18:24.704 --> 18:26.005
[ Laughs ]

18:26.038 --> 18:27.740
We're gonna take her down
together.

18:27.774 --> 18:29.876
We're an
unstoppable team.

18:29.909 --> 18:31.311
[ Laughs ]

18:36.583 --> 18:41.921
**

18:41.954 --> 18:43.390
Did you have me
stand back there

18:43.423 --> 18:45.124
so you could use my bad luck
to make Cheryl lose?

18:51.664 --> 18:53.132
I am?

19:04.477 --> 19:06.913
We can make a real dent.
Who's next?

19:06.946 --> 19:08.581
**

19:14.287 --> 19:15.588
Pass the Normandy butter?

19:15.622 --> 19:17.757
Go to hell.

19:17.790 --> 19:19.125
Sorry to interrupt
your dinner.

19:19.158 --> 19:20.593
How did you get in here?

19:20.627 --> 19:22.495
We're not here to discuss
your lack of home security.

19:22.529 --> 19:23.963
We're here to apologize.

19:23.996 --> 19:25.265
[ Scoffs ]

19:25.298 --> 19:26.833
I'm not interested
in your apology.

19:26.866 --> 19:29.502
I know it was selfish,
but we didn't want to see

19:29.536 --> 19:31.238
our best friends go
into kid jail

19:31.271 --> 19:32.605
just as we were
getting out of it.

19:32.639 --> 19:35.107
If you want to have a baby,
we support you.

19:35.141 --> 19:36.676
You'll be great parents.

19:36.709 --> 19:38.778
Sorry! Shop's closed.

19:38.811 --> 19:40.580
I have Nicole --
one and done.

19:40.613 --> 19:42.215
I know,
and Nicole's amazing.

19:42.249 --> 19:43.783
But just think
of how incredible

19:43.816 --> 19:45.151
it would be to have a baby
with Honey.

19:47.320 --> 19:50.490
Pumpkin...
I know you're mad at me,

19:50.523 --> 19:54.126
but I'm just nervous
about my life changing.

19:54.160 --> 19:56.596
I know you'd be
a great mom,

19:56.629 --> 19:59.399
but I'm just not sure if
I'm ready to be a father again.

20:00.833 --> 20:02.435
I'm nervous, too.

20:02.469 --> 20:05.305
I never thought I wanted kids,
like, ever.

20:05.338 --> 20:06.706
[ Both chuckle ]

20:06.739 --> 20:09.709
But then I met you,
and that changed.
Hmm.

20:09.742 --> 20:12.144
Look, you may not
be sure you're ready,

20:12.178 --> 20:14.281
but together,
we're ready.

20:14.314 --> 20:16.416
I think we are, too.

20:16.449 --> 20:19.352
So, let's untie these tubes
and make a baby!

20:19.386 --> 20:20.487
Ahh!

20:20.520 --> 20:22.689
[ Both laugh ]

20:22.722 --> 20:24.891
I say this with love,
but please,

20:24.924 --> 20:27.026
never interfere
in our lives again.

20:27.059 --> 20:30.229
I say this with love --
no promises.

20:30.263 --> 20:31.698
So, I'm just gonna get
right into it.

20:31.731 --> 20:34.367
Can I go to the Michigan Womyn's
Music Festival next weekend?

20:34.401 --> 20:35.968
It's a woman's-only event
celebrating the crossroads

20:36.002 --> 20:37.504
between music and femininity.

20:37.537 --> 20:38.738
Tori Amos is playing

20:38.771 --> 20:40.540
the Nair Hair Removal stage
Saturday night.

20:40.573 --> 20:42.475
Dad, you like her,
you saw her on TV and said,

20:42.509 --> 20:43.910
"Who's the mermaid
on the keys?"

20:43.943 --> 20:45.378
And I said,
"That's Tori Amos."

20:45.412 --> 20:47.380
I should have said, "She's
playing at the Womyn's Festival"

20:47.414 --> 20:48.915
and asked you about it then,
but I didn't.

20:48.948 --> 20:50.249
So here we are.

20:50.283 --> 20:51.418
Anyway,
it's all on the flier,

20:51.451 --> 20:52.719
which I'm gonna leave here
for you to read.

20:54.587 --> 20:55.922
It's, uh...

20:55.955 --> 20:57.290
[ Door closes ]

21:00.993 --> 21:04.397
**

21:04.431 --> 21:05.698
Two days.

21:05.732 --> 21:07.867
We paid for
15 years of storage,

21:07.900 --> 21:09.936
and the couch lasted
two days.

21:09.969 --> 21:11.838
Do you want me to find out
which one of them did it?

21:11.871 --> 21:13.906
No, we'll just
ground all of them.

21:13.940 --> 21:14.774
I guess we still can't have

21:14.807 --> 21:16.142
nice things.

21:16.175 --> 21:17.510
I'll flip the cushion.

21:17.544 --> 21:18.778
Don't.

21:18.811 --> 21:20.647
That's where my water broke,
remember?

21:20.680 --> 21:22.782
Eddie somehow managed
to ruin the couch

21:22.815 --> 21:24.751
even before he was
on this earth.
